---
import SidebarLayout from '../../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';
import "../../../styles/global.css";
---

<SidebarLayout app="css">
  <h1 class="text-xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-5 text-custom-accent text-center">
    CSS Tutorials
  </h1>

  <section class="mb-5 space-y-6 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed text-custom-secondary">
    <p>
      <strong class="text-custom-primary">Cascading Style Sheets (CSS)</strong> is the language used to style and layout web pages. It controls the presentation of HTML elements, including colors, fonts, spacing, and responsive design.
    </p>

    <p>
      CSS works alongside HTML and JavaScript to create modern, visually appealing websites. With CSS, you can transform plain HTML into beautiful, professional-looking web pages.
    </p>

    <p>
      In this tutorial series, you'll explore:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-4">
      <li>CSS selectors and basic syntax</li>
      <li>Box model and layout fundamentals</li>
      <li>Modern layout systems like Flexbox and Grid</li>
      <li>Responsive design techniques</li>
      <li>Animations and transitions</li>
      <li>Advanced CSS features</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6 mt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mb-3">Why Learn CSS?</h2>
      <p>
        CSS is essential for web development. It gives you complete control over the visual appearance of your websites. Whether you're building a simple blog or a complex web application, CSS skills are indispensable.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        Modern CSS with Flexbox, Grid, and CSS variables has revolutionized web layout, making it easier than ever to create responsive, maintainable designs.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</SidebarLayout>